Phase 1: Initial Setup and Planning  Repository Setup You already have a repository at https://github.com/sivrikayahukuk/sivrikayahukuk/pulls. Verify if this repository will serve as the starting point for your project. If not, we can create a new repository. Define Core Objectives Draft a detailed README for the repository: Project Goal: Build and interconnect 6-15 agents using workflows and RPA to form a circular business model. Summary of Tools: Mention GitHub Spark, Claude Cowork, and other tools/libraries you plan to use. Workflow List: Define the types of agents and workflows you envision. Select the Right Frameworks Choose tools/frameworks for each component: RPA: UiPath, Automation Anywhere, or Python RPA Libraries (e.g., PyAutoGUI, RPAFramework). Agents: Use Python or Node.js (for multi-agent systems consider frameworks like Rasa, LangChain). Workflow Orchestration: Tools like Apache Airflow, Prefect, or n8n (no-code/low-code workflow automation). Branch Structure Create branches for each major component: setup-environment workflow-engine agent-development  Phase 2: Environment and Agent Prototyping Environment Setup Define your setup scripts for dependency installation. Example initial libraries for Python: pip install fastapi uvicorn pytest pip install rpa-python langchain  Prototype Agents Define 1-2 minimalist agents to test: # agent_example.py import time def agent_task(): while True: print("Agent Task Running...") time.sleep(5) Collaborate Using GitHub Spark Utilize GitHub Spark to track contributions and code reviews as the agents grow.  Phase 3: Workflow Development Design Flexible Workflows Map workflows visually using tools like Lucid Chart or Miro. Implement basic workflows using the chosen orchestration framework: from airflow import DAG from airflow.operators.python_operator import PythonOperator  Inter-agent Communication Define how agents will communicate: REST API (e.g., FastAPI). Message Queues (e.g., RabbitMQ, Kafka).  Connect to RPA Frameworks Ensure your agents can trigger robotic processes: Example: Automating invoice processing or managing emails.  Phase 4: Circular Business Model Define Circular Feedback Loops Connect outputs from workflows as new inputs for another. Agents can update shared databases or trigger follow-up processes.  Test the Full System Deploy test cases to verify every agent and workflow meets your expectations.